{
  "stem": "22869.7",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "One.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Now, I'm going to get her.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So my task was now, again, to jump from truck and train and go on foot to reach a certain city where I heard that she is there-- staying there.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I made it in a few days.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I don't remember exactly what it was-- two or three days-- where I met her.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And she brought home from concentration camp a girlfriend who-- she designated, while she was in camp, that, if she ever comes out alive, she designated that girl to be my brother's wife.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It sounds-- it sounds funny, but that's the truth.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And the truth is that she later on married my brother Joe.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we came home.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And we started running a household.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So now, of course, we get back.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "There are some other people who survived and came back to town and were beginning to build the religious life again, around us.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "You know, you can't find a person who was a ritual slaughterer to come get some kosher food.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But you can live on other items than-- than meat and still maintain a certain kind of a kosher home.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And my sister, who was older than I am, tried to get me back to-- to get back in the steps that I left over when we left our hometown, to, little by little, come back into religion, go back to start putting on your phylacteries, your tefillin, daily, and do your daily prayers.",
      "word_count": 54
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "It took a little while.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "It wasn't so easy.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It took a short while until I shook all this, what shall I say-- 'foreign thinking,' I will call it for the lack of a better word.",
      "word_count": 27
    }
  ],
